July 22, Beijing.
Daxingzhuang Town, Pinggu District, Beijing, forcibly demolished houses on farmers' homesteads. Several villagers bravely resisted on their own roofs, which aroused cheers from the surrounding people.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Netizens added the details of the incident: Those who shouted were all veterans of the Shanghai Armed Police (or their families). At that time, the army allocated houses near the army to eligible soldiers. However, more than ten years later, at the beginning of this year, the army suddenly said that there was a new rule five years ago, stipulating that the army must return the house to the army after demobilization, but for some reason it was only implemented on a large scale at the beginning of this year. The army, together with the public security and government agencies, put pressure on veterans to return the houses (because almost all veterans go to the public security and government agencies), using their jobs, pensions, and even their children's jobs as threats, and the directors, deputy directors, and political commissars of the units took turns to talk to them. Therefore, many people could not withstand the pressure and returned the houses, and another group of people tried to find a way to jointly petition.
